// Trivial alias parser. Use when a built-in does exactly what you need and you just
// want a vendor-named entrypoint.
//
// Any reference to /logParsers/MyJSONBased now resolves to the built-in `json`.
//
// Caveats:
//   - aliasTo cannot chain (target must be a real parser, not another alias).
//   - aliasTo is MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE with everything else — including the required
//     default attributes (metadata.version, dataSource.category, dataSource.name,
//     dataSource.vendor). If you need those attributes to land on every event, you
//     cannot use aliasTo. Instead, copy the built-in's body into a full parser and
//     add the attributes block.
//   - Practical guidance: use aliasTo only for throwaway/demo cases where the
//     downstream pipeline does NOT require the default attributes. For production
//     use, prefer a full parser with the required defaults.

{
  aliasTo: "json"
}
